      • smoothDisparity

        private void smoothDisparity(Mat oldDisp,
                             Mat newDisp,
                             double min,
                             double max)
        Smoothen the disparity that might change too much from frame to frame. The idea is to look around the pixel in a 20x20 square to find the previous max value, if it changed more than that the disparity need smoothing (otherwise an object might pop from front to back each frame
        Parameters:
        oldDisp - is the last frame's disparity map
        newDisp - is the current disparity map of the frame being computed and will be directly modified through this function
        min - is the minimum disparity value
        max - is the maximum disparity value
